{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":761,"text":"I want to tell you three stories"},{"time":3273,"text":"about the power of relationships"},{"time":5749,"text":"to solve the deep and complex\nsocial problems of this century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10062,"text":"You know, sometimes it seems\nlike all these problems"},{"time":12999,"text":"of poverty, inequality, ill health,\nunemployment, violence, addiction --"},{"time":17812,"text":"they're right there in one person's life."},{"time":20662,"text":"So I want to tell you about someone\nlike this that I know."},{"time":24367,"text":"I'm going to call her Ella."},{"time":26460,"text":"Ella lives in a British city\non a run down estate."},{"time":30190,"text":"The shops are closed, the pub's gone,"},{"time":32408,"text":"the playground's pretty desolate\nand never used,"},{"time":34731,"text":"and inside Ella's house,\nthe tension is palpable"},{"time":37581,"text":"and the noise levels are deafening."},{"time":39605,"text":"The TV's on at full volume."},{"time":41443,"text":"One of her sons is fighting\nwith one of her daughters."},{"time":43999,"text":"Another son, Ryan, is keeping up this\nconstant stream of abuse from the kitchen,"},{"time":47794,"text":"and the dogs are locked\nbehind the bedroom door and straining."},{"time":50999,"text":"Ella is stuck."},{"time":52735,"text":"She has lived with crisis for 40 years."},{"time":55319,"text":"She knows nothing else,\nand she knows no way out."},{"time":59077,"text":"She's had a whole series\nof abusive partners,"},{"time":61750,"text":"and, tragically, one of her children has\nbeen taken into care by social services."},{"time":66091,"text":"The three children\nthat still live with her"},{"time":68387,"text":"suffer from a whole range of problems,\nand none of them are in education."},{"time":71886,"text":"And Ella says to me that she\nis repeating the cycle"},{"time":74907,"text":"of her own mother's life before her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77695,"text":"But when I met Ella,\nthere were 73 different services"},{"time":80999,"text":"on offer for her and her family\nin the city where she lives,"},{"time":84161,"text":"73 different services\nrun out of 24 departments in one city,"},{"time":88454,"text":"and Ella and her partners and her children\nwere known to most of them."},{"time":91788,"text":"They think nothing of calling\nsocial services"},{"time":93926,"text":"to try and mediate one of the many\narguments that broke out."},{"time":96802,"text":"And the family home was visited\non a regular basis by social workers,"},{"time":100275,"text":"youth workers, a health officer,\na housing officer, a home tutor"},{"time":104999,"text":"and the local policemen."},{"time":106999,"text":"And the governments say\nthat there are 100,000 families"},{"time":109761,"text":"in Britain today like Ella's,"},{"time":111884,"text":"struggling to break the cycle of economic,\nsocial and environmental deprivation."},{"time":117269,"text":"And they also say\nthat managing this problem"},{"time":119467,"text":"costs a quarter of a million pounds\nper family per year"},{"time":122493,"text":"and yet nothing changes."},{"time":123889,"text":"None of these well-meaning visitors\nare making a difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126999,"text":"This is a chart we made in the same city\nwith another family like Ella's."},{"time":131306,"text":"This shows 30 years of intervention\nin that family's life."},{"time":134932,"text":"And just as with Ella, not one of these\ninterventions is part of an overall plan."},{"time":138787,"text":"There's no end goal in sight."},{"time":140258,"text":"None of the interventions\nare dealing with the underlying issues."},{"time":143333,"text":"These are just containment measures,\nways of managing a problem."},{"time":146367,"text":"One of the policemen says to me,"},{"time":148110,"text":"\"Look, I just deliver the message\nand then I leave.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":150623,"text":"So, I've spent time living\nwith families like Ella's"},{"time":153332,"text":"in different parts of the world,"},{"time":154896,"text":"because I want to know: what can we learn"},{"time":157158,"text":"from places where our social institutions\njust aren't working?"},{"time":160675,"text":"I want to know what it feels like\nto live in Ella's family."},{"time":163490,"text":"I want to know what's going on\nand what we can do differently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167525,"text":"Well, the first thing I learned\nis that cost is a really slippery concept."},{"time":171638,"text":"Because when the government says\nthat a family like Ella's"},{"time":174380,"text":"costs a quarter of a million pounds\na year to manage,"},{"time":177001,"text":"what it really means"},{"time":178176,"text":"is that this system costs\na quarter of a million pounds a year."},{"time":181170,"text":"Because not one penny of this money\nactually touches Ella's family"},{"time":184309,"text":"in a way that makes a difference."},{"time":185913,"text":"Instead, the system is just\nlike this costly gyroscope"},{"time":188480,"text":"that spins around the families,\nkeeping them stuck at its heart,"},{"time":191483,"text":"exactly where they are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193532,"text":"And I also spent time\nwith the frontline workers,"},{"time":195879,"text":"and I learned that it\nis an impossible situation."},{"time":198726,"text":"So Tom, who is the social worker\nfor Ella's 14-year-old son Ryan,"},{"time":203465,"text":"has to spend 86 percent of his time\nservicing the system:"},{"time":206999,"text":"meetings with colleagues,\nfilling out forms,"},{"time":209094,"text":"more meetings with colleagues\nto discuss the forms,"},{"time":211546,"text":"and maybe most shockingly,"},{"time":212816,"text":"the 14 percent of the time\nhe has to be with Ryan"},{"time":215409,"text":"is spent getting data\nand information for the system."},{"time":217929,"text":"So he says to Ryan,"},{"time":219104,"text":"\"How often have you been smoking?\nHave you been drinking?"},{"time":221815,"text":"When did you go to school?\""},{"time":223152,"text":"And this kind of interaction\nrules out the possibility"},{"time":225726,"text":"of a normal conversation."},{"time":226962,"text":"It rules out the possibility\nof what's needed"},{"time":229104,"text":"to build a relationship\nbetween Tom and Ryan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232999,"text":"When we made this chart,"},{"time":234412,"text":"the frontline workers,\nthe professionals --"},{"time":236451,"text":"they stared at it absolutely amazed."},{"time":238246,"text":"It snaked around the walls\nof their offices."},{"time":240999,"text":"So many hours, so well meant,\nbut ultimately so futile."},{"time":246999,"text":"And there was this moment\nof absolute breakdown,"},{"time":250463,"text":"and then of clarity:"},{"time":252319,"text":"we had to work in a different way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255652,"text":"So in a really brave step,\nthe leaders of the city where Ella lives"},{"time":258981,"text":"agreed that we could start\nby reversing Ryan's ratio."},{"time":261650,"text":"So everyone who came into contact\nwith Ella or a family like Ella's"},{"time":264834,"text":"would spend 80 percent of their time\nworking with the families"},{"time":267770,"text":"and only 20 percent servicing the system."},{"time":270359,"text":"And even more radically,"},{"time":272234,"text":"the families would lead"},{"time":273428,"text":"and they would decide who\nwas in a best position to help them."},{"time":276779,"text":"So Ella and another mother were asked\nto be part of an interview panel,"},{"time":280162,"text":"to choose from amongst\nthe existing professionals"},{"time":282509,"text":"who would work with them."},{"time":284800,"text":"And many, many people wanted to join us,"},{"time":286790,"text":"because you don't go into this kind\nof work to manage a system,"},{"time":289885,"text":"you go in because you can\nand you want to make a difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292762,"text":"So Ella and the mother asked\neverybody who came through the door,"},{"time":295999,"text":"\"What will you do when my son\nstarts kicking me?\""},{"time":298455,"text":"And so the first person who comes in says,"},{"time":300999,"text":"\"Well, I'll look around\nfor the nearest exit"},{"time":303142,"text":"and I will back out very slowly,"},{"time":305999,"text":"and if the noise is still going on,\nI'll call my supervisor.\""},{"time":309024,"text":"And the mothers go,\n\"You're the system. Get out of here!\""},{"time":311761,"text":"And then the next person who comes\nis a policeman, and he says,"},{"time":314999,"text":"\"Well, I'll tackle your son to the ground\nand then I'm not sure what I'll do.\""},{"time":318999,"text":"And the mothers say, \"Thank you.\""},{"time":320701,"text":"So, they chose professionals who confessed"},{"time":322947,"text":"they didn't necessarily have the answers,"},{"time":324941,"text":"who said -- well, they weren't\ngoing to talk in jargon."},{"time":328554,"text":"They showed their human qualities\nand convinced the mothers"},{"time":331467,"text":"that they would stick with them\nthrough thick and thin,"},{"time":334104,"text":"even though they wouldn't\nbe soft with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336187,"text":"So these new teams and the families"},{"time":337903,"text":"were then given a sliver\nof the former budget,"},{"time":340086,"text":"but they could spend the money\nin any way they chose."},{"time":342601,"text":"And so one of the families\nwent out for supper."},{"time":344860,"text":"They went to McDonald's and they sat down\nand they talked and they listened"},{"time":348489,"text":"for the first time in a long time."},{"time":350573,"text":"Another family asked the team"},{"time":352187,"text":"if they would help them do up their home."},{"time":355253,"text":"And one mother took the money"},{"time":356784,"text":"and she used it as a float\nto start a social enterprise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360335,"text":"And in a really short space of time,"},{"time":362808,"text":"something new started to grow:"},{"time":365241,"text":"a relationship between the team\nand the workers."},{"time":368163,"text":"And then some remarkable\nchanges took place."},{"time":371104,"text":"Maybe it's not surprising"},{"time":372648,"text":"that the journey for Ella has had\nsome big steps backwards"},{"time":375406,"text":"as well as forwards."},{"time":376591,"text":"But today, she's completed\nan IT training course,"},{"time":379380,"text":"she has her first paid job,\nher children are back in school,"},{"time":382692,"text":"and the neighbors,"},{"time":383867,"text":"who previously just hoped this family\nwould be moved anywhere"},{"time":386800,"text":"except next door to them,"},{"time":388030,"text":"are fine."},{"time":389205,"text":"They've made some new friendships."},{"time":391329,"text":"And all the same people have been\ninvolved in this transformation --"},{"time":395369,"text":"same families, same workers."},{"time":397999,"text":"But the relationship between them\nhas been supported to change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402556,"text":"So I'm telling you about Ella\nbecause I think that relationships"},{"time":405661,"text":"are the critical resource we have"},{"time":407622,"text":"in solving some of these\nintractable problems."},{"time":410024,"text":"But today, our relationships\nare all but written off"},{"time":412770,"text":"by our politics, our social policies,\nour welfare institutions."},{"time":416662,"text":"And I've learned that this\nreally has to change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420002,"text":"So what do I mean by relationships?"},{"time":422411,"text":"I'm talking about the simple\nhuman bonds between us,"},{"time":425439,"text":"a kind of authentic sense\nof connection, of belonging,"},{"time":427999,"text":"the bonds that make us happy,\nthat support us to change,"},{"time":430707,"text":"to be brave like Ella\nand try something new."},{"time":433535,"text":"And, you know, it's no accident"},{"time":435479,"text":"that those who run and work\nin the institutions"},{"time":438042,"text":"that are supposed to support\nElla and her family"},{"time":440324,"text":"don't talk about relationships,"},{"time":441862,"text":"because relationships are expressly\ndesigned out of a welfare model"},{"time":445958,"text":"that was drawn up in Britain\nand exported around the world."},{"time":449440,"text":"The contemporaries of William Beveridge,"},{"time":451397,"text":"who was the architect\nof the first welfare state"},{"time":453679,"text":"and the author of the Beveridge Report,"},{"time":455623,"text":"had little faith in what they called\nthe average sensual or emotional man."},{"time":459146,"text":"Instead, they trusted this idea\nof the impersonal system"},{"time":462614,"text":"and the bureaucrat who would be detached\nand work in this system."},{"time":466999,"text":"And the impact of Beveridge"},{"time":469138,"text":"on the way the modern state\nsees social issues"},{"time":471405,"text":"just can't be underestimated."},{"time":473488,"text":"The Beveridge Report\nsold over 100,000 copies"},{"time":476688,"text":"in the first weeks of publication alone."},{"time":479041,"text":"People queued in the rain\non a November night to get hold of a copy,"},{"time":482274,"text":"and it was read across the country,\nacross the colonies, across Europe,"},{"time":485664,"text":"across the United States of America,"},{"time":487429,"text":"and it had this huge impact"},{"time":489225,"text":"on the way that welfare states\nwere designed around the globe."},{"time":492846,"text":"The cultures, the bureaucracies,\nthe institutions -- they are global,"},{"time":497931,"text":"and they've come to seem\nlike common sense."},{"time":499975,"text":"They've become so ingrained in us,"},{"time":502083,"text":"that actually we don't even\nsee them anymore."},{"time":504856,"text":"And I think it's really important to say\nthat in the 20th century,"},{"time":507999,"text":"they were remarkably successful,\nthese institutions."},{"time":510660,"text":"They led to longer lifespans,\nthe eradication of mass disease,"},{"time":514115,"text":"mass housing, almost universal education."},{"time":517999,"text":"But at the same time,"},{"time":519999,"text":"Beveridge sowed the seeds\nof today's challenges."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523999,"text":"So let me tell you a second story."},{"time":525787,"text":"What do you think today is a bigger killer\nthan a lifetime of smoking?"},{"time":533226,"text":"It's loneliness."},{"time":535741,"text":"According to government statistics,\none person over 60 -- one in three --"},{"time":540681,"text":"doesn't speak to or see\nanother person in a week."},{"time":544666,"text":"One person in 10, that's 850,000 people,"},{"time":547999,"text":"doesn't speak to anyone else in a month."},{"time":550924,"text":"And we're not the only people\nwith this problem;"},{"time":553222,"text":"this problem touches the whole\nof the Western world."},{"time":555677,"text":"And it's even more acute\nin countries like China,"},{"time":557999,"text":"where a process of rapid urbanization,\nmass migration, has left older people"},{"time":561706,"text":"alone in the villages."},{"time":563274,"text":"And so the services that Beveridge\ndesigned and exported --"},{"time":567119,"text":"they can't address this kind of problem."},{"time":569430,"text":"Loneliness is like a collective\nrelational challenge,"},{"time":572064,"text":"and it can't be addressed\nby a traditional bureaucratic response."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576486,"text":"So some years ago,\nwanting to understand this problem,"},{"time":579461,"text":"I started to work with a group\nof about 60 older people"},{"time":582358,"text":"in South London, where I live."},{"time":584203,"text":"I went shopping, I played bingo,"},{"time":586302,"text":"but mainly I was just\nobserving and listening."},{"time":588489,"text":"I wanted to know\nwhat we could do differently."},{"time":591837,"text":"And if you ask them, people tell you\nthey want two things."},{"time":594689,"text":"They want somebody to go up a ladder\nand change a light bulb,"},{"time":597622,"text":"or to be there when they\ncome out of hospital."},{"time":599944,"text":"They want on-demand, practical support."},{"time":602322,"text":"And they want to have fun."},{"time":603904,"text":"They want to go out, do interesting things\nwith like-minded people,"},{"time":607146,"text":"and make friends like we've all\nmade friends at every stage of our lives."},{"time":611478,"text":"So we rented a phone line,\nhired a couple of handymen,"},{"time":614231,"text":"and started a service we called \"Circle.\""},{"time":616592,"text":"And Circle offers its local membership\na toll-free 0 800 number"},{"time":620437,"text":"that they can call on demand\nfor any support."},{"time":623190,"text":"And people have called us\nfor so many reasons."},{"time":625383,"text":"They've called because\ntheir pets are unwell,"},{"time":627526,"text":"their DVD is broken, they've forgotten\nhow to use their mobile phone,"},{"time":630824,"text":"or maybe they are coming out of hospital"},{"time":632773,"text":"and they want someone to be there."},{"time":634450,"text":"And Circle also offers\na rich social calendar --"},{"time":637624,"text":"knitting, darts, museum tours,\nhot air ballooning -- you name it."},{"time":642255,"text":"But here's the interesting thing,\nthe really deep change:"},{"time":646674,"text":"over time, the friendships\nthat have formed"},{"time":649909,"text":"have begun to replace the practical offer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652964,"text":"So let me tell you about Belinda."},{"time":654621,"text":"Belinda's a Circle member, and she was\ngoing into hospital for a hip operation,"},{"time":658881,"text":"so she called her local Circle to say\nthey wouldn't see her for a bit."},{"time":662889,"text":"And Damon, who runs the local Circle,\ncalls her back and says, \"How can I help?\""},{"time":666713,"text":"And Belinda says, \"Oh no, I'm fine --"},{"time":668648,"text":"Jocelyn is doing the shopping,\nTony's doing the gardening,"},{"time":671465,"text":"Melissa and Joe are going\nto come in and cook and chat.\""},{"time":674186,"text":"So five Circle members\nhad organized themselves"},{"time":677217,"text":"to take care of Belinda."},{"time":680123,"text":"And Belinda's 80, although she says\nthat she feels 25 inside,"},{"time":683493,"text":"but she also says"},{"time":685081,"text":"that she felt stuck and pretty down\nwhen she joined Circle."},{"time":689083,"text":"But the simple act of encouraging her\nto come along to that first event"},{"time":693588,"text":"led to a process where\nnatural friendships formed,"},{"time":696812,"text":"friendships that today are replacing\nthe need for expensive services."},{"time":701157,"text":"It's relationships\nthat are making the difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705572,"text":"So I think that three factors\nhave converged"},{"time":708504,"text":"that enable us to put relationships\nat the heart and center"},{"time":711520,"text":"of how we solve social problems today."},{"time":714389,"text":"Firstly, the nature of the problems --"},{"time":716476,"text":"they've changed, and they require\ndifferent solutions."},{"time":719155,"text":"Secondly, the cost, human as much\nas financial, of doing business as usual."},{"time":723669,"text":"And thirdly, technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726009,"text":"I've talked about the first two factors."},{"time":728553,"text":"It's technology that enables\nthese approaches to scale"},{"time":731525,"text":"and potentially now support\nthousands of people."},{"time":734911,"text":"So the technology we've used\nis really simple,"},{"time":737094,"text":"it's made up of available things\nlike databases, mobile phones."},{"time":740571,"text":"Circle has got this very simple\nsystem that underpins it,"},{"time":743331,"text":"enables a small local team to support\na membership of up to a thousand."},{"time":747215,"text":"And you can contrast this\nwith a neighborhood organization"},{"time":750012,"text":"of the 1970s,"},{"time":751193,"text":"when this kind of scale\njust wasn't possible,"},{"time":753380,"text":"neither was the quality or the longevity\nthat the spine of technology can provide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757520,"text":"So it's relationships\nunderpinned by technology"},{"time":760773,"text":"that can turn the Beveridge\nmodels on their heads."},{"time":763710,"text":"The Beveridge models are all\nabout institutions with finite resources,"},{"time":767380,"text":"anonymously managing access."},{"time":769845,"text":"In my work at the front line,"},{"time":771489,"text":"I've seen again and again how\nup to 80 percent of resource"},{"time":775199,"text":"is spent keeping people out."},{"time":777258,"text":"So professionals have to administer"},{"time":778972,"text":"these increasingly complex forms\nof administration"},{"time":781390,"text":"that are basically about stopping people\naccessing the service"},{"time":784756,"text":"or managing the queue."},{"time":786930,"text":"And Circle, like the relational services\nthat we and others have designed,"},{"time":791290,"text":"inverts this logic."},{"time":792679,"text":"What it says is, the more people,\nthe more relationships,"},{"time":796696,"text":"the stronger the solution."},{"time":799734,"text":"So I want to tell you my third\nand final story,"},{"time":802120,"text":"which is about unemployment."},{"time":805300,"text":"In Britain, as in most places\nin the world,"},{"time":808090,"text":"our welfare states were primarily designed"},{"time":810654,"text":"to get people into work,"},{"time":813323,"text":"to educate them for this,"},{"time":815339,"text":"and to keep them healthy."},{"time":817035,"text":"But here, too, the systems are failing."},{"time":819592,"text":"And so the response has been"},{"time":820988,"text":"to try and make these old systems\neven more efficient and transactional --"},{"time":824549,"text":"to speed up processing times, divide\npeople into ever-smaller categories,"},{"time":828205,"text":"try and target services at them\nmore efficiently -- in other words,"},{"time":831400,"text":"the very opposite of relational."}]},{"cues":[{"time":835425,"text":"But guess how most people find work today?"},{"time":839583,"text":"Through word of mouth."},{"time":841399,"text":"It turns out that in Britain today,\nmost new jobs are not advertised."},{"time":846024,"text":"So it's friends that tell you about a job,"},{"time":848191,"text":"it's friends that recommend you for a job,"},{"time":850488,"text":"and it's a rich and diverse social network\nthat helps you find work."},{"time":854803,"text":"Maybe some of you here\nthis evening are thinking,"},{"time":857152,"text":"\"But I found my job through an advert,\""},{"time":859037,"text":"but if you think back, it was probably\na friend that showed you the ad"},{"time":862383,"text":"and then encouraged you to apply."},{"time":863984,"text":"But not surprisingly,"},{"time":865331,"text":"people who perhaps most need\nthis rich and diverse network"},{"time":868634,"text":"are those who are most isolated from it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871357,"text":"So knowing this,"},{"time":872656,"text":"and also knowing about the costs\nand failure of current systems,"},{"time":875702,"text":"we designed something new\nwith relationships at its heart."},{"time":878675,"text":"We designed a service\nthat encourages people to meet up,"},{"time":884061,"text":"people in and out of work,"},{"time":885525,"text":"to work together in structured ways"},{"time":887300,"text":"and try new opportunities."},{"time":890308,"text":"And, well, it's very hard to compare\nthe results of these new systems"},{"time":894303,"text":"with the old transactional models,"},{"time":895999,"text":"but it looks like,\nwith our first 1,000 members,"},{"time":898324,"text":"we outperformed existing services\nby a factor of three,"},{"time":901239,"text":"at a fraction of the cost."},{"time":903223,"text":"And here, too, we've used technology,"},{"time":906127,"text":"but not to network people in the way\nthat a social platform would do."},{"time":909549,"text":"We've used it to bring people face to face\nand connect them with each other,"},{"time":913175,"text":"building real relationships\nand supporting people to find work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":918308,"text":"At the end of his life, in 1948,"},{"time":921279,"text":"Beveridge wrote a third report."},{"time":923913,"text":"And in it he said he had made\na dreadful mistake."},{"time":928356,"text":"He had left people\nand their communities out."},{"time":933111,"text":"And this omission, he said,\nled to seeing people,"},{"time":937740,"text":"and people starting to see themselves,"},{"time":939899,"text":"within the categories\nof the bureaucracies and the institutions."},{"time":943708,"text":"And human relationships\nwere already withering."},{"time":947296,"text":"But unfortunately, this third report\nwas much less read"},{"time":950536,"text":"than Beveridge's earlier work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":953115,"text":"But today, we need to bring people\nand their communities"},{"time":957350,"text":"back into the heart of the way\nwe design new systems and new services,"},{"time":961501,"text":"in an approach that I call\n\"Relational Welfare.\""},{"time":964032,"text":"We need to leave behind\nthese old, transactional,"},{"time":966572,"text":"unsuitable, outdated models,"},{"time":968854,"text":"and we need to adopt instead\nthe shared collective relational responses"},{"time":972389,"text":"that can support a family like Ella's,"},{"time":974869,"text":"that can address an issue like loneliness,"},{"time":977200,"text":"that can support people into work\nand up the skills curve"},{"time":979959,"text":"in a modern labor market,"},{"time":981427,"text":"that can also address challenges\nof education, of health care systems,"},{"time":985589,"text":"and so many more of those problems\nthat are pressing on our societies."},{"time":990306,"text":"It is all about relationships."},{"time":993324,"text":"Relationships are the critical\nresource we have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":996375,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":997550,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}